<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="add_help_chapter">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>add_help_chapter</refname>
    <refpurpose> Add an entry in the helps list</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>add_help_chapter(title,path[,mode])</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>title</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a character string, the help chapter title</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>path</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a character string, the path of the directory containing the
       help files.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>mode</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a boolean, %T if the help directory belongs to scilab modules list, %F else (toolboxes). The default value is %F.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
  This function adds a new entry in the helps list. The help chapter
  files are to be located in a single directory. If the given
  <literal>title</literal> already exists in the helps list associated with
  the same path nothing is done.  The function checks if the directory
  exist.</para>
  </refsection>
